<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,774,848,956]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,258,848,869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,241,848,869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
–
</emphasis>
Male sixth tergite with single prickly, anteriad curved projection at anteroventral corner (
<figureCitation box="[454,510,877,898]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[136,180,2034,2055]" captionTargetBox="[140,1471,1058,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-8@4.[102,1509,1030,2016]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 6–10. Phortica (Phortica) ni Chen &amp; Toda, new species, male: 6, sixth tergite in ventral view; 7, epandrium and cercus in lateral view; 8, surstylus in frontal view; 9, tenth sternite and additional plate in frontal view; 10, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere and aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333046/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); lateral process of paramere ca. 2/3 as long as apical one, apically with 1 sensillum and 1 black spine (
<figureCitation box="[201,274,935,956]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[136,180,2034,2055]" captionTargetBox="[140,1471,1058,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-8@4.[102,1509,1030,2016]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 6–10. Phortica (Phortica) ni Chen &amp; Toda, new species, male: 6, sixth tergite in ventral view; 7, epandrium and cercus in lateral view; 8, surstylus in frontal view; 9, tenth sternite and additional plate in frontal view; 10, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere and aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333046/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
