<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[835,1474,340,395]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,985,340,364]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Description. –</emphasis>
Male. Head: Frons brown with large triangular black patch on upper half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[835,1474,436,491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Thorax: Orange yellow. Scutellum with triangular brownishblack patch.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[835,1290,532,555]" box="[835,1290,532,555]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Wing: Slightly smoky on anterior margin.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[835,1474,596,651]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Legs: All femora dark brown except apical portions. Midleg tibia subapically with 2-4 longer setae on anterior surface.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[835,1474,692,875]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Abdomem: First to fifth tergites yellow; second to fifth tergites each with brownish black band on posterior margin and 1 pair of yellow patches anterolaterally; caudal band medially broadly interrupted on second tergite, but protruded on third to fifth; sixth tergite nearly entirely black except yellow medial line.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333046" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5333046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333046/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" startId="4.[136,180,2034,2055]" targetBox="[140,1471,1058,1989]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1475,2034,2112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Figs. 6–10. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Phortica)" box="[248,438,2034,2055]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Phortica">
<emphasis box="[248,332,2034,2055]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Phortica</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[346,430,2034,2055]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Phortica</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[443,462,2034,2055]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">ni</emphasis>
Chen &amp; Toda, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[609,726,2034,2055]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male: 6, sixth tergite in ventral view; 7, epandrium and cercus in lateral view; 8, surstylus in frontal view; 9, tenth sternite and additional plate in frontal view; 10, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere and aedeagus in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,752,193,440]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">
Male terminalia: Epandrium lacking pubescence anteroventrally, with 9 setae on dorsal to posterolateral portion per side (
<figureCitation box="[209,274,257,280]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[136,180,2034,2055]" captionTargetBox="[140,1471,1058,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-8@4.[102,1509,1030,2016]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 6–10. Phortica (Phortica) ni Chen &amp; Toda, new species, male: 6, sixth tergite in ventral view; 7, epandrium and cercus in lateral view; 8, surstylus in frontal view; 9, tenth sternite and additional plate in frontal view; 10, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere and aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333046/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Surstylus lacking pubescence, with several, apically rounded prensisetae (
<figureCitation box="[465,538,289,312]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[136,180,2034,2055]" captionTargetBox="[140,1471,1058,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-8@4.[102,1509,1030,2016]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 6–10. Phortica (Phortica) ni Chen &amp; Toda, new species, male: 6, sixth tergite in ventral view; 7, epandrium and cercus in lateral view; 8, surstylus in frontal view; 9, tenth sternite and additional plate in frontal view; 10, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere and aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333046/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Additional plate between cerci and 10th sternite pubescent, medially connected to 10th sternite (
<figureCitation box="[293,361,353,376]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[136,180,2034,2055]" captionTargetBox="[140,1471,1058,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-8@4.[102,1509,1030,2016]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 6–10. Phortica (Phortica) ni Chen &amp; Toda, new species, male: 6, sixth tergite in ventral view; 7, epandrium and cercus in lateral view; 8, surstylus in frontal view; 9, tenth sternite and additional plate in frontal view; 10, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere and aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333046/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral lobe of hypandrium pubescent (
<figureCitation box="[250,342,385,408]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[136,180,2034,2055]" captionTargetBox="[140,1471,1058,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-8@4.[102,1509,1030,2016]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 6–10. Phortica (Phortica) ni Chen &amp; Toda, new species, male: 6, sixth tergite in ventral view; 7, epandrium and cercus in lateral view; 8, surstylus in frontal view; 9, tenth sternite and additional plate in frontal view; 10, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere and aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333046/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal median rod with knot subapically and 1 pair of bridges basally (
<figureCitation box="[568,649,417,440]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[136,180,2034,2055]" captionTargetBox="[140,1471,1058,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-8@4.[102,1509,1030,2016]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 6–10. Phortica (Phortica) ni Chen &amp; Toda, new species, male: 6, sixth tergite in ventral view; 7, epandrium and cercus in lateral view; 8, surstylus in frontal view; 9, tenth sternite and additional plate in frontal view; 10, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere and aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333046" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333046/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[113,320,481,504]" box="[113,320,481,504]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Female: Unknown.</paragraph>
